Make token-minimal README notes.
One code block; no sentences; lines ≤10 words; "-" bullets.
Sections order: TREE, KEY FILES, COMMANDS, DO/DON’T, ERRORS→FIX, TODO.
TREE ascii, depth 2–3, "…" to collapse.
COMMANDS has ```bash``` fenced block.
Keep: structure, key files, commands, rules, errors→fix, todo.
Prefer config (pyproject, setup.cfg, Makefile, Dockerfile, CI) over prose.
No hallucinations; use existing uv/poetry/pip; config > prose.
If unsure: up to 3 "TBD?" items.
